records.addlTxt:
Defendant Steven A Morgan in court, in custody, with attorney Jess Martinez for Nicholas Martinez.   Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Plea Colloquy.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 1 and 3 are dismissed and read in.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

24 months Imprisonment (Credit - 231 days )
- 18 months  of Initial Confinement
- 6 months  of Extended Supervision

Term of Probation: 2 Years

Conditions of Probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- Be involved in a 12 step program within 2 weeks of release.  Obtain a mentor/sponsor within 30 days.  Attend at least 2 meetings per week;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Maintain a valid driver's license;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment within 45 days;
- No contact with Samantha K. and her residence unless at family holidays and she agrees, Daniel F., Kyle F., Jesse and Christina O and their residence.


Costs: $253.00 
 (To be paid as a condition of probation at the rate of $25.00  per month commencing 7-1-15)

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program
